Don't let chance to salvage S.Sudan go to waste South Sudan profile Another resident said some civil servants had not been paid for four months, and the government should have spent the money on their salaries. Presidential spokesman Ateny Wek Ateny told BBC Newsday that the it had been budgeted for and it was "nonsensical" to suggest that South Sudan's ruling elite was wasting money. The MPs would repay the loans over five years, just as they had repaid similar loans given to them in 2005 and 2009 to buy cars, Mr Ateny said. "Mobility is part of the rights of the parliamentarian," he added.